Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.04,0:00:11.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Emcee: Simoun{\i0}\NI wonder whose\N"true natures" we'll expose today?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.64,0:00:16.27,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Emcee: Simoun{\i0}\NToday's guests,\Nplease call out the title of this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.35,0:00:17.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,Monthly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.48,0:00:18.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,ADR.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.82,0:00:19.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Bulletin!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.39,0:00:21.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Monthly! ADR Bulletin Special{\i0}\NBulletin!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.09,0:00:24.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Monthly! ADR Bulletin Special{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.89,0:00:25.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hello, everybody. I'm Ami\NKoshimizu, and I play Paraietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.56,0:00:28.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Paraietta: Ami Koshimizu{\i0}\NHello, everybody. I'm Ami\NKoshimizu, and I play Paraietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.76,0:00:32.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kaim: Michiko Hosokoshi{\i0}\NHi, I'm Michiko\NHosokoshi, and I play Kaim.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.50,0:00:35.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, that was kind of weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.60,0:00:37.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why was it from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.84,0:00:41.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway,\Nthis is part 2 of the series...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.14,0:00:44.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,We'll be taking over this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.61,0:00:48.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I heard part 1 with Aer and\NNeviril was pretty relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:49.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,The theme was "laid-back."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.75,0:00:50.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then we'II...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.58,0:00:52.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then we'II...\NI think we should do an efficient show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.75,0:00:53.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.95,0:00:56.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don't think we're\Nup to it, but they know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.76,0:00:57.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.09,0:00:59.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,We'll give it a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.86,0:01:02.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,So anyway, hope you enjoy the show!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.46,0:01:08.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay, we're gonna{\i0}\N{\i1}start with this corner...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.67,0:01:10.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,No-Holds-Barred!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.74,0:01:17.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,No-Holds-Barred!?\NBrutal, Live Talk Show.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.51,0:01:25.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Have you ever fallen{\i0}\N{\i1}in love with another woman?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.32,0:01:29.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know if you'd\Ncall the feeling falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.76,0:01:32.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,When I see\Na really gorgeous woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.89,0:01:35.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,...I think, "Amazing..." or "How cool."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.06,0:01:38.79,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think, "I wish I could be like that."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.90,0:01:42.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Or I find it somehow\Nhealing to be near her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.14,0:01:44.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,I've felt that,\Nbut whether that's "love"...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.07,0:01:49.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,True, it's also how far you\Ngo before calling it love, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.58,0:01:51.20,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.94,0:01:52.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.01,0:01:56.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,"I really like you. Just being\Nwith you makes me feel great."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.42,0:01:57.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,But would I want to kiss her?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.95,0:01:59.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,But would I want to kiss her?\NThat's another matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.59,0:02:05.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,But if you could categorize love as\Neverything except for that kind... kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.39,0:02:06.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oops...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.16,0:02:08.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,Oops...\NSpeak clearly now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.19,0:02:10.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,I'm a voice actress by profession!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.86,0:02:12.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Um... right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.63,0:02:17.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then if you leave out\Ncertain stuff like kissing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.57,0:02:23.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you can call that love, you can't\Nrule out falling in love with women.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:28.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you're a voice actress,{\i0}\N{\i1}then speak like a professional!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.78,0:02:29.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,This one!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.35,0:02:31.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,This one!\NWhoa, you faked me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:32.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Extreme! Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.89,0:02:36.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Were you uncomfortable{\i0}\N{\i1}doing extreme scenes?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:41.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,The most extreme one was where\Nwe went, "Vroom... pow, pow, pow!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.93,0:02:44.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's the most extreme!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.30,0:02:45.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Which episode was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.03,0:02:47.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Six?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.07,0:02:48.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Was it six or so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:52.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,We... It was a Paraietta-\Nand Kaim-centric episode...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.57,0:02:59.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,...and the two of us were totally\Npretending to fly in a Simoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:03.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,We were playing, our two characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:08.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,And our lines were like,\N"Vroom, pow-pow-pow, blam, vroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.06,0:03:12.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Like grammar school kids going,\N"Vroom! This is my plane!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:15.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,The two of us were\Nplaying this kids' game...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:20.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,And though she's not the type to do it,\NParaietta goes "pow-pow-pow!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.00,0:03:24.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,"There's an enemy there!"\N"Okay, pow-pow-pow!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.24,0:03:27.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,So we played that scene,\Nand I agree it was pretty extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:29.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,Like, "We're gonna get trashed!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:31.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,But really, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.58,0:03:34.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,To tell the truth,\Nthat was the most embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.15,0:03:42.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sorry to interrupt as it's getting good,{\i0}\N{\i1}but we're going to the next corner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.59,0:03:44.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why Oh Why!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.89,0:03:46.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why Oh Why!?\NSimoun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.13,0:03:48.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.03,0:03:51.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, time for a quiz, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.16,0:03:51.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.90,0:03:53.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,Seems so.\NOkay, let's start.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.70,0:03:55.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,Simoun, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:56.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let's quiz.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:04:01.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What's a "chor"?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.48,0:04:04.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,When you go "ding, ding."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:07.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, when you call.\NWe're a little off on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.25,0:04:11.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's like when you\Naddress your butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:13.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,"Sebastian!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.62,0:04:16.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,It's so trendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.26,0:04:18.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,When you shoot a soccer ball...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:19.45,Regular,,0,0,0,,Goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.56,0:04:20.75,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:26.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Just give us\Nan answer already, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.03,0:04:30.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,You'd never go off track, Ami.\NYou weren't, Ami.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:32.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Really? Yeah, you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:36.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Quit it. We're supposed to be\Nunited today. Today, it's two for one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.34,0:04:38.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, a "chor" is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.58,0:04:41.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,To be specific, it refers to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.71,0:04:46.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,The sibyllae as\Na team is called a "chor."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.99,0:04:52.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Correct{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.79,0:04:53.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,You didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.19,0:04:54.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is a "chor"?{\i0}\N{\i1}A unit/team{\i0}\NYou didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:04:56.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is a "chor"?{\i0}\N{\i1}A unit/team{\i0}\NWell, I knew there was a Chor Rubor...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.70,0:04:58.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is a "chor"?{\i0}\N{\i1}A unit/team{\i0}\N...but couldn't explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.60,0:05:01.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is a "chor"?{\i0}\N{\i1}A unit/team{\i0}\NSee? It's a unit or a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:05.23,Regular,,0,0,0,,Like "Team Whatever."\N"Team So-and-so."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.34,0:05:08.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,I get it.\NWhat was our team's name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.91,0:05:09.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.68,0:05:11.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Chor Tempest.\NOh, yeah! Close call.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.84,0:05:15.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,How can you remember Chor Rubor's\Nname and not Chor Tempest's?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.52,0:05:20.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Time to tell everyone about{\i0}\N{\i1}our CD. Advertise efficiently!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:26.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,This here is Toshihiko Sahashi's\N"The Dazzling Tango of Passion"!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.12,0:05:28.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,As well as "The Majestic Symphony".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.80,0:05:29.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,The music that's played in {\i1}Simoun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.00,0:05:31.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Simoun Original Soundtrack 1\NThe music that's played in {\i1}Simoun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.63,0:05:35.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Simoun Original Soundtrack 1\NThe {\i1}Simoun{\i0} original soundtrack part 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.10,0:05:40.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,This CD will be released on June 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:40.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,We hope you enjoy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:43.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,We hope you enjoy it!\NPlease, please buy it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.08,0:05:48.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Things were pretty{\i0}\N{\i1}laid-back this time around too...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.68,0:05:52.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Okay, good work today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.42,0:05:53.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.55,0:05:56.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have to say we were really efficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.39,0:05:58.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Such a brisk pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.82,0:06:03.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,But I do think we did\Na fun show... How about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.20,0:06:08.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I had a good time! I was like,\N"Is it okay to enjoy myself this much?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.37,0:06:10.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,Was that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.17,0:06:11.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,It wasn't like a show.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.07,0:06:16.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,It was more like the two of us having\Na private conversation or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.91,0:06:19.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,Still, I hope you all enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:22.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since it's a "live talk show" after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.55,0:06:26.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,About this particular DVD,\Nwhich is about to be released...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.92,0:06:31.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since the feature itself is still\Nbeing broadcast to rave reviews...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:35.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,...please keep watching as you wait\Nfor the DVDs a-comin'... coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.53,0:06:38.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,A-comin'? A-comin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.56,0:06:42.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,Can Paraietta talk like that?\N"They shall come out."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.14,0:06:45.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,They shall come out,\Nand I believe they will be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:47.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's it. Let's go with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.54,0:06:50.37,Regular,,0,0,0,,So please, please support {\i1}Simoun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.48,0:06:51.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.24,0:06:53.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.21,0:06:55.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Simoun{\i0} Bulletin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.78,0:06:59.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, let's end this right.\NMonthly ADR Bulletin!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.99,0:07:00.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.02,0:07:01.99,Regular,,0,0,0,,Ready...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.05,0:07:05.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Monthly ADR Bulletin!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.76,0:07:06.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Don't miss the next show!!{\i0}
